

To test if ROS is installed properly and works correctly; IF you have not done so

Steps:

1. Open a new terminal window (Ctrl + Alt + t) and enter

$ roscore

2. Run turtlesim_node in the turtlesim package; Open a new terminal window and enter:

$ rosrun turtlesim turtlesim_node

3. Run turtle_teleop_key in the turtlesim package; Open a new terminal window and enter:

$ rosrun turtlesim turtle_teleop_key

You can use any of arrow keys on the keyboard (←, → , ↑, ↓) to move the turtle

4. Run rqt_graph in the rqt_graph package; Open a new terminal window and enter:

$ rqt_graph

The rqt_graph node shows information about the currently running nodes in a GUI form;
Circle represents a node (program) and square represents a topic (message
communication)


